HEADWORD: Thirlage
<hw>Thirl"age</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Thrall</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Scots Law)</fld> <def>The right which the
owner of a mill possesses, by contract or law, to compel the tenants of
a certain district, or of his sucken, to bring all their grain to his
mill for grinding.</def> <rj><au>Erskine.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

